definition[0]: relating to products or services that are more expensive and of better quality than other products of the same type
definition[1]: if a figure, amount etc is at the high end of what people expected it to be, it is near the top of that range
example[1]: The company’s fourth-quarter profit was near the high end of analysts’ estimates of 11 to 14 cents a share.
definition[2]: the high end of a market or product range consists of the most expensive products in that market or range
example[2]: The company continued to aim at the high end of the dishwasher market, where sales weren’t large but profits were.
definition[3]: high-end products are the most expensive ones in a particular market or range
example[3]: a maker of high-end car stereo equipment
